Italy bank lending up 2 . 9 pct Jan - Sept - Ciampi . Italian bank lending rose 2 . 9 percent in the first nine months of the year , Treasury Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi said on Thursday . In the three year period between 1993 and 1995 bank lending rose an annual average 2 . 0 percent . Ciampi said the slow growth rate was not so much due to the state of the economy as to a growing tendency among firms to reduce their banking debts . The Treasury minister said losses in the banking sector over the past three years amounted to 46 trillion lire . Ciampi said bad loans rose 15 percent year - on - year in August with the ratio between bad loans and all loans climbing above the 10 percent threshold . - - Rome newsroom + 396 6782501 
